# ───────────────────────── Data / Models — Guardrails ────────────────────

# Keep REAL datasets/models visible to DVC (do NOT ignore these by default).

# If you must exclude a specific derived subset, add a precise pattern below.

# data/\*\*            ← typically MANAGED by DVC (do not ignore)

# models/\*\*          ← typically MANAGED by DVC (do not ignore)

# ───────────────────────── Safety Notes ───────────────────────────────────

# • DVC will ignore these patterns; Git may still see them unless also in .gitignore.

# • Never add real datasets/models to .dvcignore unless you intend to keep them external.

# • Prefer `dvc add data/...` and `dvc.yaml` stages for controlled artifacts.

